cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with information theory and coding, specifically multiple descriptions and erasure channels. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses vector Gaussian MD, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of layered coding suggests cs.SI (Signal Processing) as a possible category. The paper also presents achievable schemes based on codes, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of multiple receivers suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible category.
